title.en-US: Equipping Workshop (Cont.)

description.en-US:
How do we challenge individuals to take the next step in their walk with Christ and find a clear path toward discipleship? Come learn how Watermark seeks to equip our Members to be and make disciples in any life stage. Watermark’s Equipping Team will discuss transformative Bible studies, devotional and apologetic strategies, faithful stewardship, and other opportunities to equip your church with a deeper understanding of God’s Word.

*Workshops require advance registration during conference signups.*

internalTitle.en-US: Marriage (Merge, Foundation Groups, re|engage) Workshop - Tuesday

title.en-US: Marriage (Merge, Foundation Groups, re|engage) Workshop (Cont.)

description.en-US:
Learn about Watermark's unique marriage ministries and practical steps to lead couples in your church more effectively. Whether you want to improve your existing marriage ministry, overhaul your strategy, or start from the ground up, this workshop will help you make disciples in the context of marriage and the local church.

*Workshops require advance registration during conference signups.*

internalTitle.en-US: The Church's Role in Healthcare - Breakout Session 2

title.en-US: The Church's Role in Healthcare

description.en-US:

*Duplicate from Breakout Session 1*

title.en-US: The Benefits of Being Employed by the Church

description.en-US:

*Duplicate from Breakout Session 1*

title.en-US: Breakout Session 2
Global Missions Overview

description.en-US:
Find out more about Watermark’s non-traditional approach to global missions and how God has transformed thousands of lives in our efforts to reach “the ends of the earth.”

*Duplicate from Breakout Session 1*

internalTitle.en-US: The Church's Role In Community Development - Breakout Session 2

title.en-US: The Church's Role In Community Development

description.en-US:
Are you frustrated with providing handouts to under-resourced individuals? Do you see the same people in your community day after day and wish you could make a real difference in their lives? Does your city view your church as a resource that really helps the community in effective ways? Join us as we explore some key principles in learning how the body of Christ can be deployed in long term impact in your community to really make a difference in the lives of those you seek to serve.

*Duplicate from Breakout Session 1*

title.en-US: Caring for the Vulnerable in our Communities

description.en-US:

*Duplicate from Breakout Session 1*

title.en-US: Marriage Ministry Overview

description.en-US: From preparing nearly-weds, establishing newlyweds, and enriching all marriages, we will discuss the "why" behind our marriage ministry model and how this strategy can transform the health of marriages in your church and community.

title.en-US: Staff Consulting Appointments

description.en-US:
We are making our staff members from every ministry area available to you. That includes our senior leaders, finance coordinators, IT team, student directors, and everything in between! We don't claim to have all the answers, but if you want to hear a different perspective, bounce some ideas off someone else, or hear what's worked (and what hasn't worked) in our experience, sign up for a time slot.

[Reserve your spot now!](clc://clc/app-link/NodeSingle?nodeId=Event:d24d97963372a28c4618c149248498678c264fc08e10b965e4abe78c15632b10) Don't wait long to reserve your time. Slots will fill up quickly.

title.en-US: Recovery (re:generation) Workshop

description.en-US:
In Christ, people can be set free from the destruction of sin. Learn about the radical healing people are receiving in Christ through re:generation, our Biblical 12-step recovery ministry. Through the gospel, daily abiding, authentic community, confession, repentance, and forgiveness, entire churches can change and grow. 

*Workshops require advance registration during conference signups.*

internalTitle.en-US: ProLife, Foster Care, and Adoption Workshop (The Life Initiative)

title.en-US: ProLife, Foster Care, and Adoption Workshop (The Life Initiative)

description.en-US:
Learn the needs of your church and county and the assets to discover where you should develop a continuum of care specific to your area, engage with women and men whose stories intertwine with these issues, and discuss how to develop prolife and family restoration initiatives in your church or community.

*Workshops require advance registration during conference signups.*

title.en-US: Worship Arts Workshop

description.en-US:
No matter the size, tradition, or style of your church, learn and discuss why the core values of your church should affect the worship ministry, why it’s vital to have your identity found in Christ and not in your talent, how to shepherd your worship teams, how to audition and develop more worship leaders and musicians, how to lead a rehearsal, and more.

*Workshops require advance registration during conference signups.*
